Maybe we could rewrite these methods to be more generic and named similiar to reactive-streams methods (which allows to extract them to some utils file and not clutter this class)? E.g.
```
    private fun <A, B> Either<A, B>.doOnLeft(action: () -> Unit): Either<A, B> =
            apply { if (isLeft()) action() }

    private fun <A> Option<A>.doOnEmpty(action: () -> Unit): Option<A> =
            apply { if (isEmpty()) action() }
```
This could be then used as
```
router
    .findDestination(msg)
    .doOnEmpty { metrics.notifyMessageDropped(ROUTE_NOT_FOUND) }


 MessageValidator
    .validateProtobufMessage(it)
    .doOnLeft { metrics.notifyMessageDropped(INVALID_MESSAGE) }

```
